benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Add custom fields to account

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC13, @TC14, @TC16, @TC20, @TC21, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC29, @TC30 cover successful creation with valid payloads and headers.

Invalid Payload: @TC08 (malformed JSON), @TC09 (empty body), @TC10 (non-existent account), @TC11 (unsupported fields), @TC12 (duplicate fields), @TC16 (unauthorized), @TC18 (SQL injection), @TC19 (XSS), @TC28 (unexpected data types), @TC30 (null values) cover various invalid input scenarios.
Edge Cases: @TC26 (empty array), @TC27 (partial input), @TC28 (unexpected data types), @TC29 (max/min values), @TC30 (null values) cover boundary and special cases.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens beyond @TC16.
Rate Limiting: No tests for multiple rapid requests or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Service Unavailability: No tests simulating API or dependency failures (@TC17 is general but not specific to POST).
Concurrency: No tests for simultaneous requests or race conditions.
Response Time & Performance: No explicit performance or load testing scenarios.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling with large custom fields payloads.
Include explicit authorization tests with missing or invalid tokens.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system stability under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation.
Simulate service outages or dependency failures during POST requests.
Create concurrency tests to check for race conditions and data consistency.
Include performance testing for response times under various loads.
